# You normally DON'T need this file.
#
# Credentials come from the project's murk vault: `npm run dev` sources ../.env
# (which exports MURK_KEY_FILE) and runs Next under `murk exec`, injecting the
# R2_* secrets. The Models tab reads R2 with those.
#
# This file is only for overrides when you're NOT using murk (e.g. CI, or a
# different bucket). Copy to .env.local and set what you need:

# R2_ACCOUNT_ID=
# R2_ACCESS_KEY_ID=
# R2_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=
# R2_BUCKET=momentarily

# Point the Status tab at a non-prod feed:
# NEXT_PUBLIC_FEED_BASE=https://feed.momentarily.nyc

# Override the vault path used by the @iicky/murk-secrets fallback:
# MURK_VAULT=../.murk
